1. üî¥ #1: Introduction to Node JS in Hindi | Node.JS Tutorial for Beginners in Hindi in 2020

* What is Node JS ?
- Node.js is a Javscript runtime built on Chrom  e V8 Javascript engine. The runtime environment is literally just the environment your application is running in. V8 engine is a javscript engine which converts Javscript code into machine understandable so that it should run on outside browser. 

- Node.js is a javascript running on the server. NodeJS is not a framework nor a language nor a library. It is just a runtime environment.

* When to use Node JS?
- I/O bound ( Node JS is single threaded also it can handle multiple thread request and it is non blocking meaning you can send multiple request at same time asynchronous output.)

- Data Streaming Applications (Applications like instagram whose data is non ending when you scroll data is there always.)
- Real time chat Applications (Like whatsapp etc.)

