4. Node.JS #4: üìë Complete REPL in NodeJS | READ, Eval, Print & Loop in NodeJS in Hindi in 2020

* Node JS REPL
- REPL stands for Read Eval Print Loop and it represents a computer environment like a Windows console or Unix/Linux shell where a command is entered and the system responds with output in an interactive mode.

- The REPL feature of Node is very useful in experimenting with Node.JS codes and to debug Javscript codes.

Read - Reads user's input, parses the input into JavaScript data-structure, and stored in memory.

Eval - Takes and evaluates the data-structure.

Print - Prints the result.

Loop - Loops the above command until the user presses ctrl-c twice.

- To run nodejs project use command
node index.js

- To enter in REPL you have run command
node

Now you have entered in REPL then use .help to know more commands. You can exit repl using following command.
.exit

- REPL
1. js Expression
2. use variables
3. Multiline code
4. use (_) to get the last result 
Ex. 10 + 5
> 15
_ + 5
> 20

5. we can use editor mode.

5. üî¥ #5: Mastering the Node.js Core Modules | File System Node.js Module in Hindi in 2020

* NodeJS Core Module.
- Consider modules to be same as Javascript libraries. A set of functions you want to include in your applications.

- Node.js has a set of built in modules which you can use without any further installation.

- The Node.js file system module allows you to work with the file system on your computer.

To include the File System module, use the require() method:
var fs = require('fs');

- A common use for the File System module:

Read files
Create files
Update files
Rename files

- Node.js includes an additional data type called buffer which is not available in browser's javascript.
Buffer is mainly used to store binary data.
While reading from a file or receiving packets over the network.

