16. üî¥ #16: Creating Our Own Web Server in Node.JS | HTTP Module in Node JS in Hindi in 2020

- To access web pages of any web application, you need a web server. The web server will handle all the http requests for the web application.

- IIS is a web server for ASP.NeT web application and Apache is web server for PHP or Java web applications.

- Node.js provides capabilities to create your own web server which will handle HTTP requests asynchronously. You can use IIS or Apache to run Node.js web application but it is recommended to use Node.js web server. 

- A web server is a software program which serves web pages to web users (browsers).

21. Streams and Buffer in Node JS

- Streams are objects that let you read data from a source or write data to a destination in continuos fashion. In Node.JS there are four types of streams.

Streaming means listening to music or watching video in 'real time', instead of downloading a file to your computer and watching later.

Readable - Stream which is used for write operation.

Writable - Stream which is used for write operation.

Duplex - Stream which can be used for both read and write operation.

Transform - A type of duplex stream where the output is consumed based on input.

- Each type of Stream is an EventEmitter instance and throws several events at different instance of times. For rxample some of the commonly used events are - 

data - This event is fired when there is data is available to read.

end - This event is fired when there is no more data to read.

error - This event is fired when there is any error receiving or writing data.

finish - This event is fired when all the data has been flushed to underlying system.

- stream.pipe(), the method used to take a readable stream and connect it to a writeable stream.


Express JS

1. üî¥ #1: Express JS Introduction, Setup, IDE & First Program in Express JS Tutorial in Hindi in 2020

- What is Express.JS
* Express.js is a Node.js framework. It's the most popular framework as of now (the most starred on NPM).

* ExpressJS is a web application framework that provides you with a simple API to build websites, web apps and back ends.

- Why do we actually need Express.js? How it is useful for us to use with Node.js?

* Try to write a small REST API server in plain Node.js, using only core modules and then in ExpressJS. The latter will take you 5-10x less time and lines of code.

- Difference between res.json() and res.send()?
* The methods are identical when an object or array is passed, but res.json will also convert non-objects, such as null and undefined, which are not valid JSON.

- Use of express.static()
- Use of template engines (Pug, hbs, EJS, handlebar.js)
